Siya Mlambo was snatched by two men who took him during a robbery when his mother arrived home from work.Police spokesman Mpande Khoza said police received information on Thursday that the missing child might be at Madadeni in Newcastle.Police drove to KwaZulu-Natal and recovered the child who was unharmed. His name had been changed.Khoza said two men believed to be cousins of the family were arrested in Madadeni and a nanny was arrested in Soweto. We are still looking for one suspect who is on the run but is known to us. TMG Digital